MARSS Model to Iterpolate Missing Streamflow Observations

Thomas Buehrens

Last Updated 11/05/2022.

Setup

All analyses require R software (link) (v3.4.3) for data retrieval, data processing, and summarizing model results. Here we configure R to perform our analysis and generate our outputs

options(width = 100)
knitr::opts_chunk$set(message = FALSE)
set.seed(123)

We also need a couple of helper functions which we will load from the functions folder, which we will load using the walk() function from the purrr package (which we will install if it is not already installed).

wd_functions<-"functions"
sapply(FUN = source, paste(here::here(),wd_functions, list.files(wd_functions), sep="/"))

Here we will load & install packages we need to use (needs internet connection if packages not already installed)

                        flow_params ="discharge",
                        daily_or_instantaneous= "daily",
                        begin_date = "2002-10-01",
                        end_date = "2022-09-30"
                        )


flow_dat<-naselle%>%
  dplyr::select(date,flow_cfs)%>%
  mutate(river="naselle")%>%
  bind_rows(grays%>%
              dplyr::select(date,flow_cfs)%>%
              mutate(river="grays")
              )%>%
  bind_rows(elochoman%>%
              dplyr::select(date,flow_cfs)%>%
              mutate(river="elochoman")
              )%>%
  bind_rows(abernathy%>%
              dplyr::select(date,flow_cfs)%>%
              mutate(river="abernathy")
              )%>%
  bind_rows(chehalis_doty%>%
              dplyr::select(date,flow_cfs)%>%
              mutate(river="chehalis_doty")
              )%>%
  group_by(river,date)%>%
  summarise(flow_cfs=mean(flow_cfs),.groups = "keep")%>%
  ungroup()

MARSS Model

Here we use a MARSS model to interpolate missing or bad flow data.

marss_dat<-flow_dat%>%
  dplyr::select(river,date,zl_flow_cfs)%>%
  pivot_wider(names_from = river,values_from = zl_flow_cfs,id_cols=date)%>%
  arrange(date)%>%
  mutate(jdate=julian(date))%>%
  filter(year(date)>2015 & year(date) <= 2017)

all_dates<-tibble(jdate=julian(min(marss_dat$date)):julian(max(marss_dat$date)))

marss_dat<-all_dates%>%
  left_join(marss_dat)

marss_mat<-marss_dat%>%
  dplyr::select(-c(date,jdate))%>%
  as.matrix()%>%
  t()


model=list(
 Q= "equalvarcov",#"unconstrained"
 R= "diagonal and equal",
 U= matrix(rep(0,nrow(marss_mat)),nrow=nrow(marss_mat),1)
)
fit=MARSS(marss_mat, model=model)

fitted<-t(fit$states)
colnames(fitted)<-gsub("X.","mle_",colnames(fitted))

marss_dat<-marss_dat%>%
  dplyr::select(-jdate)%>%
  bind_cols(fitted)%>%
  pivot_longer(cols=c(everything(),-date),names_to = "river")%>%
  mutate(type=ifelse(grepl("mle_",river),"mle","obs"))%>%
  mutate(river=gsub("mle_","",river))%>%
  pivot_wider(values_from =value,names_from = type)%>%
  arrange(river,date)

scale_params<-flow_dat%>%
  group_by(river)%>%
  summarise(mu_l=mean(log(flow_cfs)),
            sd_l=sd(log(flow_cfs))
  )

marss_dat<-marss_dat%>%
  ungroup()%>%
  left_join(scale_params)%>%
  mutate(mle_rescaled=exp(mle*sd_l+mu_l))%>%
  left_join(flow_dat%>%
              dplyr::select(date,river,flow_cfs)
              )

write.csv(marss_dat,"marss_dat.csv")

Plot Flow Data with MARSS Predictions

ggplot(marss_dat,aes(x=date,y=mle_rescaled,color=river))+
  geom_line()+
  geom_point(aes(y=flow_cfs),size=0.6,color="black")+
  facet_wrap(~river, scales = "free_y")+
  scale_y_log10()+
  ylab("flow (cfs)")+
  theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 90))+
  theme_bw()+
  annotation_logticks(sides = "l")
